definitions.definition: Indicating that one's preceding statement was false and that one has successfully fooled one's interlocutor .
examples: Here, have fifty dollars. Psych! That was two dollars!
I broke up with my ex girl. Here's her number. Psych! That's the wrong number!
Psych! I just found my missing bracelet!

main_definition: ( slang ) Indicating that one's preceding statement was false and that one has successfully fooled one's interlocutor .
secondary_definitions: ( dated , slang ) An interjection of surprised happiness.
